content.description: Shared start with Obesity Direct, but move left instead with some steep moves.
content.location: Far left overhang on the boulder.

content.description:
This is the direct start to Obesity, and it makes a really really good problem in its own right.  The movement is classic, and it could easily get four stars if it weren't overshadowed by the longer and more flowy original line.

Start on a chalked blocky jug straight beneath the end of Obesity.  Throw a right heel, move your hands up, and pull the powerful rockover into holds halfway across Obesity's traverse.  Finish with with the power endurancy finish throw and top out.

The moves are all quite accessible as far as V8 goes, and I would recommend giving it a few tries if you've gotten Obesity and have some extra time.
SDS in the middle of the face on a nice large right-facing sidepull down low.  From here, follow the slopers up and left to a throw to a big block and top out from here.
content.location: It is on the unmistakable Fraggle Rock boulder, one of the closest boulders to the road leading to the east forest parking area.  The boulder is also one of lowest in elevation in the clearcut.

content.description: A straightforward, excitingly tall problem. Start on a big jug and move up and right, finishing with sidepulls.
content.location: The vertical face left of the tree.

content.description:
Sitstart on lowest jugs on arete just to the right of

Bob's Balls

and

Obesity

. Head up arete using finger slots on the side of the arete and topout.  Scary high topout with a bad landing.
content.protection: Use more than two pads if you have them and a spotter.
content.location: It is on the unmistakable Fraggle Rock boulder, one of the closest boulders to the road leading to the east forest parking area.  The boulder is also one of lowest in elevation in the clearcut.

content.description: The farthest right problem, start with a low undercling and small rail, then simple moves to top out.
content.location: Mossy right edge of the boulder.

content.description: Sds on the right facing pinch towards the bottom of the wall as for Obesity. Make a big move out right to a large flake system that goes 3/4 of the way up the problem. From the end of the flake make a committing move to some scary holds which lead to better holds up high on the face. Do a committing rock over for the top out and then pat yourself on the back.
content.protection: The landing for this boulder is bad and there's a very committing move up top. Bring pads. Bring spotters. Bring a cool head.
content.location:
Up a faint trail to the left (if you're heading uphill) marked by a small rock pile. Bob's Balls shares a start with and is just to the right of

Obesity

.

content.description: Start wide with right hand on a sloping edge and left on a positive sidepull. Move into a triangular feature then up and left. Finish high and right through underclings and blocky jugs.
content.location: The south face of the boulder, around the right side if looking at Obesity
